Metzen wrote:Why do they have to be tidally locked? Mercury is not Tidally locked to our sun. I don't think we understand enough about how things become tidally locked to make assumptions about far away worlds yet.Depends on how narrowly you define tidal locking. Mercury is locked into a 3:2 spin-orbit resonance (it rotates 3 times per 2 orbits of the sun). Mercury isn't tidally locked only if you define tidal locking as strictly a 1:1 ratio.
